    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1934-09-04T17:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1934-09-04T17:00:00-05:00" n="69"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d69">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">611.1831/24a: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Minister in Costa Rica</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Sack</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-09-04T18:00:00-04:00"
                            >September 4, 1934—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>35. Please inquire of the Costa Rican Government whether it is prepared to
                    initiate at an early date exploratory conversations looking to the negotiation
                    of a commercial agreement. Since this Government is planning to give public
                    notice shortly of the intention to negotiate agreements with other Central
                    American countries it seems <pb facs="0157" n="91" xml:id="pg_91"/> appropriate
                    to inquire as a matter of courtesy whether the Costa Rican Government desires a
                    similar announcement to be made with respect to that country.</p>
                <p>Please rush reply.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Moore</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
